103.text: - I have things to do outside the appartment complexe, are we done ?
- Right, he came by in the morning.
- He just wanted to talk about work, I let him in but nothing happened.
- What’s wrong with that ? I did what’s written on the door. Nothing more, nothing less.

104.text: - I work in construction, not that you would know anything about your residents, warden
- Have the neighbours complained ? He tends to raise the volume far too much.

105.text: What do you want. I have done nothing wrong. You have no right to bother me.
